	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-08-25T09:33:28">Blue Planet Investment Trust plc, formerly Blue Planet International Investment Trust plc, is a United Kingdom-based investment company. The Company's objective is to provide investors with a combination of capital growth and income. In order to achieve its objective, the Company invests in securities, including equities, exchange traded funds, equity-related securities, bonds and derivatives issued by companies, governments and other types of issuers located across the world. The Company invests in a range of sectors, such as financials, information technology, consumer discretionary, utilities, energy, industrial, telecommunication services, healthcare, materials and consumer staples, among others. The Company has operations in the United Kingdom, the United States, France, Ireland, China, the Netherlands, Bermuda, Germany, Greece, Argentina, Nigeria and Australia. Blue Planet Investment Management Ltd is the manager of the Company.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-12-14T03:08:48">BRIEF: For the six months ended 31 October 2015, Blue Planet Investment Trust PLC revenues decreased from -L702K to -L2.8M. Net loss increased from L1.4M to L3.4M. Revenues reflect Unrealised gains decrease from -L3.2M to -L6.5M, Exchange gains / (losses) decrease from L392K to -L44K, Interest receivable decrease from L15K to L0K. Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items decreased from -L0.03 to -L0.07.</Text>
